<EnemyInfo>
  <Name>Shutter V2 (Vertical)</Name>
  <Description>
    A vertical pipe/shutter that moves and blocks the path. It can be triggered by a timer or Samus proximity. This is a more advanced version of the Shutter V1. 

    There is a bug when shooting this enemy in any of the non-Shot trigger modes will cause the shutter SFX to play. This can be fixed by changing $A2:F0C1 from 0x41 to 0x44.

    There is a strange check (likely a bug) in the code at $A2:F06A to suppress the sound effect for the auto trigger going downwards. It is checking for enemy ID 0xD83F, which never runs this code. It was probably supposed to be 0xD83F which does run this code and uses 0xD83F graphics. Although it is not clear sure why such a feature would exist.
  </Description>
  <Speed1>
    <Property>
      <Name>Trigger Mode</Name>
      <Description>Method to use to trigger initial movement. This generally does not affect the subsequent auto triggers, that "Proximity" mode. "Shot Multiple" does not behave correctly with the Auto timers enabled. Speed boost, Shine sparks, and psuedo-screw, power bombs all count as being shot.</Description>
      <Mask>0x00FF</Mask>
      <NameValues>
        <NameValue Value="0" Name="Timer"/>
        <NameValue Value="1" Name="Proximity"/>
        <NameValue Value="2" Name="Immediate"/>
        <NameValue Value="3" Name="Shot Single"/>
        <NameValue Value="4" Name="Shot Multiple"/>
      </NameValues>
    </Property>
    <Property>
      <Name>Distance</Name>
      <Description>Distance to move in pixels.</Description>
      <Mask>0xFF00</Mask>
    </Property>
  </Speed1>
  <Speed2>
    <Property>
      <Name>Trigger</Name>
      <Description>In proximity mode, this is pixels in horizontal distance to trigger. In timer mode, this is the number of frames before triggering.</Description>
      <Mask>0xFFFF</Mask>
    </Property>
  </Speed2>
